name: RESOURCE ThickenUp 1.2g
description:
Nestle Health Science RESOURCE ThickenUp Clear is the clear solution for dysphagia.  Our exclusive patented xanthan gum formulation offers a clear solution for patients and clinicians. RESOURCE ThickenUp Clear is a food for special medical purposes for the dietary management of people with swallowing difficulties. Instant Food and Drink Thickener. Transparent ,  tasteless ,  odourless and lump-free. Easy to mix and easy to measure. Rapid thickening and stabilisation. Innovative Technology: Patented process and exclusive Xanthan-gum blend. Its proven amylase resistance ensures stable consistency during the entire swallowing process.  Improves Compliance: Does not affect colour ,  taste and odour of hot or cold liquids or foods.

usage:
- First add desired quantity of powder into empty container (glass).
- Then add liquid into container (glass) and stir with a spoon until completely dissolved

1 sachet = 1.2 g
For pureed food add RESOURCE® ThickenUp® Clear as needed to achieve appropriate consistency.
Easy to Use: One dosage per thickening level for all liquids*. Stabilises rapidly and remains stable. Dissolves in oral nutritional supplements.
* Refer to a health care professional when mixing protein containing liquids (eg oral nutritional supplements and milk), carbonated and alcoholic beverages. These liquids behave uniquely when prepared with RESOURCE® ThickenUp® Clear.  It is the responsibility of the person administering RESOURCE® ThickenUp® Clear to ensure that the liquid is mixed to the appropriate consistency.

name: OPTIFAST VLCD Shake 18
ingredients: Vanilla Flavour: Skimmed Milk Powder (31%), Milk Proteins [Calcium Caseinate (20%), Sodium Caseinate (10%)], Maltodextrin (Corn), Vegetable Oil (Canola, Sunflower), Minerals (Potassium Citrate, Magnesium Carbonate, Calcium Phosphate, Sodium Chloride, Potassium Phosphate, Ferric Pyrophosphate, Copper Gluconate, Zinc Sulphate, Manganese Sulphate, Sodium Fluoride, Potassium Iodide, Sodium Molybdate, Sodium Selenite, Chromium Chloride), Vegetable Gum (414), Fructo-Oligosaccharide, Inulin, Medium Chain Triglycerides, Glucose Syrup (Corn), Sugar, Fish Oil, Flavour, Emulsifiers (472c, Soy Lecithin, 471), Sweeteners (Aspartame, Acesulfame Potassium), Antioxidants (301, 304, 306), Vitamins (Vitamin E Acetate, Nicotinamide, Calcium Pantothenate, Sodium Ascorbate, Pyridoxine Hydrochloride, Thiamine Hydrochloride, Vitamin A Acetate, Riboflavin, Folic Acid, Phytomenadione, Cholecalciferol, Cyanocobalamin, Biotin), Colour (Curcumin). Contains Milk, Soy and Fish. Contains Phenylalanine. May contain Egg. Gluten-free.
usage:
Add one sachet of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ to 200-250mL of cold or warm water. Stir, blend or shake to dissolve. Do not use boiling water. All prepared products should be tightly covered and consumed within 6 hours at room temperature or within 24 hours if refrigerated. Note: Do not change proportions. Follow preparation instructions. Discard any unfinished product that has been heated.
Very Low Energy Diet: For Intensive Level of the program, replace all meals with three OPTIFAST® VLCD™ products per day. Additionally, consume a minimum of two litres of calorie-free fluid and at least two cups of low starch vegetables with one teaspoon of vegetable oil per day. A program of regular light exercise enhances wellbeing and the likelihood of success. One serve of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ Shake can be replaced with one serve of any other product in the OPTIFAST® VLCD™ range (Desserts, Soups, Bars).

name: OPTIFAST VLCD Bars
description:
These delicious and convenient Bars are one the products in the OPTIFAST VLCD range.
The Bars are part of a nutritionally complete Program, are high in protein, a good source of fibre and conveniently ready to eat.
OPTIFAST VLCD should be taken under the supervision of a healthcare professional.
Very Low Energy Diet. Take an additional two litres of calorie-free fluid each day. Unsuitable for use by Pregnant or Lactating Women, Infants, children, Adolescents or People Older than 65 years of age. People with existing medical conditions, please consult your Healthcare Professional before use.
ingredients:
Chocolate Bar: Milk Proteins, Milk Chocolate (15%) [Sugar, Cocoa Solids (6%), Whole Milk Powder, Emulsifier (Soy Lecithin), Flavour], Polydextrose, Sorbitol, Glycerol, Minerals (Potassium Citrate, Calcium Carbonate, Sodium Citrate, Sodium Phosphate, Magnesium Hydroxide Carbonate, Magnesium Carbonate, Magnesium Phosphate, Calcium Phosphate, Copper Sulphate, Iron Pyrophosphate, Potassium Iodate, Sodium Selenate, Zinc Oxide, Manganese Sulphate), Cocoa Powder (5%), Vegetable Oils (Rapeseed, Safflower), Fructose Syrup, Soy Protein Isolate, Glucose Syrup, Flavour, Vitamins (Ascorbic Acid, Vitamin E Acetate, Niacinamide, Vitamin A Acetate, Calcium Pantothenate, Biotin, Cyanocobalamin, Folic Acid, Cholecalciferol, Pyridoxine Hydrochloride, Riboflavin, Phylloquinone, Thiamin Mononitrate), Emulsifier (Soy Lecithin).
Contains Milk and Soy. May contain Tree Nuts, Peanuts and Oats.
Flavours: Cappuccino, Berry Crunch, Cranberry, Assorted, Chocolate
usage:
Instructions
Open wrapper and consumer bar. OPTIFAST VLCD bars are convenient and ready to eat. One bar is equivalent to one meal on the OPTIFAST VLCD Program.
Very Low Energy Diet: For Intensive Level of the program, replace all meals with three OPTIFAST VLCD products per day. Additionally, consume a minimum of two litres of calorie-free fluid and at least two cups of low starch vegetables with one teaspoon of vegetable oil per day. A program of regular light exercise enhances wellbeing and the likelihood of success. One serve of OPTIFAST VLCD Bar can be replaced with one serve of any other product in the Optifast® VLCD™ range (Desserts, Soups, Shakes).

name: OPTIFAST VLCD Soup 53g Sachet
description:
The easy to prepare Soup products are part of the OPTIFAST VLCD range and a perfect option for a savoury, hot and satisfying meal that can be enjoyed at any time of the day. The Soups come in 3 delicious flavours Chicken, Tomato Country Style and Vegetable.
They are part of a nutritionally complete Program, that is high in protein, is a source of fibre.
OPTIFAST VLCD should be taken under the supervision of a healthcare professional.
Very Low Energy Diet.Take an additional two litres of calorie-Free fluid each day. Unsuitable for use by Pregnant or Lactating Women, Infants, children, Adolescents or People Older than 65 years of age.
ingredients: Tomato Flavour Soup: Milk Proteins [Calcium Caseinate (20%), Sodium Caseinate (10%)], Skimmed Milk Powder (24%), Tomato (8.5%), Minerals (Potassium Citrate, Sodium Chloride, Calcium Phosphate, Magnesium Oxide, Potassium Phosphate, Ferric Pyrophosphate, Zinc Sulphate, Copper Gluconate, Manganese Sulphate, Sodium Fluoride, Potassium Iodide, Sodium Selenite, Sodium Molybdate, Chromium Chloride), Vegetable Oil (Canola, Sunflower), Maltodextrin (Potato, Corn),  Vegetable Gum (414), Colours (Beetroot, Curcumin), Fructo-Oligosaccharide, Inulin, Medium Chain Triglycerides, Glucose Syrup (Corn), Sugar, Fish Oil, Parsley, Emulsifiers (472c, Soy Lecithin, 471), Antioxidants (301, 306, 304), Flavours, Vitamins (Vitamin E Acetate, Nicotinamide, Calcium Pantothenate, Sodium Ascorbate, Pyridoxine Hydrochloride, Thiamine Hydrochloride, Vitamin A Acetate, Riboflavin, Folic Acid, Phytomenadione, Cholecalciferol, Cyanocobalamin, Biotin).  Contains Milk, Soy and Fish. May contain Egg. Gluten-free.
usage:
For best results, add one sachet of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ to 200-250mL of cold water in a shaker.  Shake vigorously.  Pour soup into a microwaveable bowl or cup.  Microwave on high for 20 seconds then stir contents.  Keep heating in 20 second intervals, stirring after each time, until desired temperature is reached.  Do Not Boil.
Alternatively, add one sachet to 200-250ml cold water, stir vigorously with a whisk, gently heat on the stove whilst stirring until desired temperature is reached. Do Not Boil.
All prepared products should be tightly covered and consumed within 6 hours at room temperature or within 24 hours if refrigerated.
Note: Do not change proportions. Follow preparation instructions. Discard any unfinished product that has been heated.
Very Low Energy Diet: For Intensive Level of the program, replace all meals with three OPTIFAST® VLCD™ products per day. Additionally, consume a minimum of two litres of calorie-free fluid and at least two cups of low starch vegetables with one teaspoon of vegetable oil per day. A program of regular light exercise enhances wellbeing and the likelihood of success. One serve of OPTIFAST® VLCD™ Soup can be replaced with one serve of any other product in the OPTIFAST® VLCD™ range (Desserts, Shakes, Bars).

name: BENEPROTEIN 227g
description:
Nestle Health Science BENEPROTEIN is a concentrated source of high quality protein that mixes instantly and easily with most foods and beverages. Suitable for oral use or tube feed use.
It is not nutritionally complete and should not be used as a sole source of nutrition.
Mixes instantly into most hot and cold foods and beverages.
ingredients: Unflavoured:  Whey Protein Isolate (Milk), Soy Lecithin (genetically modified). Contains Milk and Soy.
usage:
Directions for Oral Use: Stir one scoop (enclosed) of powder into at least 4 fl oz (120 ml)of a beverage or prepared soft food until dissolved.
Directions for Tube Feeding Use: Add one scoop of powder into 2-4 fl oz (60-120 ml) of water. Stir until dissolved. Administer by syringe through feeding tube. Flush afterwards with a minimum of 1-2 fl oz (30-60 mL) water.


*7g serving size equals 1 scoop.

name: VIVONEX T.E.N 80g
description:
Nestle Health Science VIVONEX  T.E.N
A low fat elemental formula containing 100% free amino acids enriched with glutamine to meet the nutritional needs of patients with gastrointestinal impairment providing 1.0 kcal/ml.
For the short term dietary management of severe chylus leakage, bowel fistulae, pre-bowel surgery, malabsorption and digestion disturbances due to gastrointestinal impairments. Can be used as an alternative to a polymeric diet when there is accelerated transit time or malabsorption.
ingredients: Maltodextrin, amino acids (L-leucine, L-glutamine, L-lysine, L-isoleucine, L-valine, L-arginine, L-aspartic acid, L-phenylalanine, L-alanine, L-proline, L-threonine, L-histidine, glycine, L-serine, L-cysteine, L-methionine, L-tryptophan, L-tyrosine), modified potato starch, minerals (calcium lactate, magnesium glycerophosphate, potassium chloride, potassium citrate, trisodium citrate dihydrate, disodium hydrogen phosphate, sodium chloride, dipotassium hydrogen phosphate, zinc sulphate, ferrous sulphate heptahydrate, copper gluconate, manganese sulphate, chromium trichloride, sodium molybdate, potassium iodide, sodium selenite), sunflower oil, stabilizer (E 331), choline bitartrate, vitamins (C, E, pantothenic acid, niacin, B6, B1, B2, A, folic acid, K, biotin, D, B12), L-carnitine, taurine, acidity regulator (E 330). Packed under protective atmosphere. May contain traces of milk.
serving_size_1: Servings Per Pack: 1 Serving Size: 80g(80g Powder + 250mL Water)
usage:
Shaker (recommended): Put 250 ml of water in a shaker. Add 1 sachet Vivonex® T.E.N. Close the shaker and shake well for 20 seconds.
Mix with fork:  Put 250 ml of water in a cup. Stir 1 sachet Vivonex® T.E.N. while mixing. Stir well for several minutes until a clear solution is obtained.
Dissolution time is 5-10 minutes. Undissolved particles can occur.
Dosage:  6 to 10 sachets per day when used as a sole source of nutrition, or as recommended by the healthcare professional.

name: NOVASOURCE Renal 237ml
description: NOVASOURCE Renal is 2.0 kcal/mL with a high protein content. It is low in sodium and potassium, and lower in phosphorus for the dietary management of individuals with chronic or acute renal disease and for those requiring electrolyte restrictions. It is nutritionally complete and calorically dense for volume restricted diets. It is suitable for oral or tube feed use.
ingredients: Vanilla:  Water, Glucose Syrup, Vegetable Oil (Low Erucic Acid Rapeseed Oil), Milk Proteins (Sodium and Calcium Caseinates), Sucrose, Soy Protein Isolates, Minerals (Potassium Citrate, Calcium Carbonate, Sodium Chloride, Magnesium Oxide, Potassium Chloride, Zinc Sulphate, Ferrous Sulphate, Copper Gluconate, Manganese Sulphate, Chromium Chloride, Potassium Iodide, Sodium Selenite, Sodium Molybdate), Emulsifier (Soy Lecithin), Stabilizers (E460, E466), Acidity Regulator (E330), Choline Chloride, Vitamins (C, E, Niacinamide, Calcium Pantothenate, B6, B2, B1, Folic Acid, Beta-Carotene, A, Biotin, D3, B12, K1), L-Carnitine, Taurine, Natural and Artificial Flavourings. Contains Milk and Soy.
usage:
RECOMMENDED DAILY INTAKE: Up to four packs a day depending on patientﾒs fluid and protein requirement or restriction, or as recommended by a healthcare professional.
SERVING INSTRUCTIONS: 
TUBE FEEDING: Pour directly into tube feeding container.  Adjust formula flow rate and volume to patientﾒs condition and tolerance.  Provide additional water to meet fluid requirements.  Avoid contamination during preparation and use.
ORAL FEEDING: Chill before serving.

name: ARGINAID Arginine Powder 9.2g Sachet
description:
Nestle Health Science ARGINAID is a fat free arginine powder designed for people with chronic wounds. Suitable for oral or tube feed use and provides 0.11 kcal/mL. ARGINAID powder is a medical food arginine module specially formulated for the dietary management of altered physiologic or metabolic conditions that respond to increased arginine intake. Nitrogen information: - One serving of ARGINAID powder provides 4.5g of the amino acid L-arginine (1.4 grams nitrogen) - A single amino acid does not meet the dietary requirement for protein. Mixes quickly and easily with water.

ingredients: Orange Flavour:  L-arginine Powder, Citric and Malic Acids, Sodium Ascorbate, Alpha-Tocopheryl Acetate (Vitamin E source), and less than 2% of Aspartame (sweetener)*, Acesulfame Potassium (sweetener), Natural and Artificial Flavour, Colour (Beet Juice, Turmeric and Annatto Extracts).  *Phenylketonurics: Contains Phenylalanine
usage:
Store unopened power packets at room temperature. After mixing, cover and refrigerate any unused portions. Use within 24 hours. Stir briskly before use.
ORAL FEEDING
Mix content of single-serving packet with 6-8fl oz of water, stir briskly and consume.
TUBE FEEDING
Mix one packet of ARGINAID® with 120-180mL warm water. Mix and administer by syringe down the feeding tube.
DOSAGE
Take 2 servings of ARGINAID® per day. Take for a minimum of 2 weeks or until the wound has healed.
Servings may vary according to individual assessment by a qualified health care provider.

name: KID ESSENTIAL 800g
description:
KID ESSENTIALS Nutritionally Complete is a nutritionally complete supplement for children aged 1 to 10 years.
It is specially formulated to contain the essential macronutrients and micronutrients children need when dietary intake is inadequate.
ingredients: Maltodextrin (Corn), Sucrose, Milk Proteins (Whey Protein, Potassium Caseinate), Vegetable Oils (Sunflower, Rapeseed), Medium Chain Triglycerides, Minerals(Calcium Carbonate, Sodium Phosphate, Calcium Chloride, Potassium Citrate, Potassium Phosphate, Magnesium Chloride, Sodium Citrate, Ferrous Sulphate, Zinc Sulphate, Manganese Sulphate, Copper Sulphate, Potassium Iodide, Sodium Selenate, Chromium Chloride, Sodium Molybdate), Stabiliser (414), Fibers (Fructo-Oligosaccharide, Inulin), Emulsifier (Soy Lecithin), Food Acid (330), Choline Bitartrate, Flavour, Fish Oil, Taurine, L-Carnitine, Vitamins (C, E, Niacin, Calcium Pantothenate, B6, B1, B2, A, Folic Acid, K1, Biotin, D3, B12), Probiotics Cultures (Bifidobacterium Longum, Lactobacillus Paracasei). Contains Milk, Soy and Fish.
serving_size_1: Servings Per Pack: 14 Serving Size: 55g(Ave Qty per 250mL serve (55g powder + 210mL water))
usage:
Instructions1. Wash hands. 2. Measure 210ml clean water (room temperature to maintain probiotic activity) and pour into a clean container.3. Measure 55g or 7 scoops of powder using the scoop (1 x scoop of Kid Essentials® = approx. 8g) provided in the tin. 4. Add the powder to the water and immediately stir until thoroughly mixed.5. Use only enclosed scoop
Dosage may vary depending on your child's nutrition requirements. For advice on the correct dosage for your child always contact your health professional.
All prepared products should be tightly covered and consumed within 6 hours at room temperature or within 24 hours if refrigerated.
Store in a cool dry place and use within 4 weeks after opening
Note: Do not change proportions.  Follow feeding instructions.

name: SUSTAGEN Diabetic Ready to Drink 237ml
description:
Nestle Health Science SUSTAGEN Diabetic is a lower carbohydrate** oral supplement specifically formulated for people with diabetes. It is high in fibre and has a low GI ,  and provides 1.0kcal/mL. If you have diabetes and haven't been eating well ,   you may benefit from SUSTAGEN Diabetic. It provides energy ,  high quality protein ,  fibre and 27 vitamins and minerals. It is high in fibre ,  lower in carbohydrate** and has a low Glycemic Index to help avoid large fluctuations in blood glucose levels. **Compared to SUSTAGEN Hospital Formula on a per serve basis. SUSTAGEN Diabetic is specifically formulated for people with diabetes who cannot meet their nutritional needs through diet modification alone. Suitable as a sole source of nutrition. Use under medical supervision. For more information visit www.sustagen.com.au.

usage:
Check use by date on pouch.
Wash hands. Shake pouch well before use. Some separation of contents may occur.
Using clean technique, hold bag at base of SpikeRight® Plus port, remove port cap, and insert tip of threaded enteral spike set.
Turn threaded enteral spike set clockwise until tightly fastened.
Use at room temperature for up to 24 hours after spiking if proper technique is used.
Do not use if container is damaged, swollen or contents are coagulated.  Store unopened at room temperature.  Avoid excessive heat.  Do not freeze. Pouch is filled to deliver 1000ml. Actual fill volume is greater to compensate for residual volume remaining after pouch is drained.
